===================================================================================
Environment:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CPU: Intel Core i3-2310M 2.10GHz
Main-Memory: 6.00 GB
Hard-Disk: 750 GB
OS: Windows 10 professional (64-bit)
Java: Java 1.7.0_45
Scala: Scala 2.11.7
IDE: Eclipse Standard Luna Service Release 2 (4.4.2)
Scala IDE for Eclipse: 4.1.1.v-2_11-201507261049-bc34267
RDBMS: PostgreSQL 9.4.4
JDBC driver: postgresql-9.4-1200.jdbc41.jar
===================================================================================

===================================================================================
Deployment:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Create a Scala project in Eclipse.
2. Import the codes into the "src" directory.
3. Add the JDBC driver "postgresql-9.4-1200.jdbc41.jar" as External JARs
4. Start the PostgreSQL and import the database.
5. Finished.
===================================================================================

===================================================================================
Run:
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. Right click the "socket/Server.scala" and select "Run As" - "Scala Application".
2. Right click the "socket/Client.scala" and select "Run As" - "Scala Application".
3. Input the SQL query in the console of Client, press "enter".
4. Return the query result.
5. Goto step 3 until you want to quit.
6. Input "quit", press "enter".
7. Finished.
===================================================================================